In a report released today, Which? says households can save hundreds of pounds by taking simple steps. The energy price cap is increasing by 54 percent next month, meaning bill hikes of almost £700 for millions of average users. A further increase is expected in October. But Which? says turning down the heating by just one degree could reduce bills by £80 to £85 per year. What is happening where you live? Find out by adding your postcode or visit InYourArea For rooms such as bedrooms, which sit empty all day, people should consider turning the radiator down to the lowest setting but not off completely. Which? also suggests, wherever possible, lowering the washing machine temperature to 20C. And it recommends turning appliances off at the power point if they're idling on standby.